@@TJvXPContainer
<TITLEIMG TJvXPContainer>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.XPControls,JVCL.PanelsBevelsAndGroups.Panels
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  A panel style control.
Description
  Use TJvXPContainer the same way you use a panel on a form. TJvXPContainer has additional properties
  to control the visual appearance of the control. TJvXPContainer is inherited from
  TJvXPCustomContainer and publishes its properties and events but does not introduce any new
  behavior.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomContainer
Summary
  Base class for panel style controls.
Description
  TJvXPCustomContainer is a base class for panel style controls with additional properties to control
  the visual appearance of the panel. Do not create instances of TJvXPCustomContainer. Instead, drop
  a control like TJvXPContainer on your form.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomContainer.Alignment
Summary
  Determines how the caption is aligned within the control.
Description
  Set Alignment to specify how the text of the control is justified within the ClientRect of the
  control.

  The effect of the Alignment property is more obvious if the WordWrap property is True and the
  control includes more than one line of text.
See Also
  Caption

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomContainer.BorderWidth
Summary
  Sets the width of the border around the Glyph.
Description
  Use BorderWidth to specify how much space is allocated around the image in Glyph. If no image is
  assigned, this property has no effect.
See Also
  TJvXPCustomContainer.Glyph, TJvXPCustomContainer.Spacing

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomContainer.BoundColor
Summary
  Indicates the color of bound lines.
Description
  Use BoundColor to specify the color to use for the border lines drawn with the BoundLines property.
See Also
  TJvXPCustomContainer.BoundLines

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomContainer.BoundLines
Summary
  Indicates which border lines are drawn.
Description
  Use BoundLines to specify which border lines are drawn in the control.
See Also
  TJvXPCustomContainer.BoundColor

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomContainer.EnabledMode
Summary
  Indicates how changing Enabled affects child controls.
Description
  Use EnabledMode to control how child controls are affected when the control's Enabled state
  changes. If EnabledMode is emAffectChilds, the Enabled state of child controls are changed to match
  the control's Enabled state.
See Also
  Enabled

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomContainer.Focusable
Summary
  Specifies if the control will receive focus when clicked.
Description
  Set Focusable to true to make the control focused when it is clicked. If Focusable is false, the
  control can only be focused by setting TabStop to true and tabbing to it.
See Also
  TabStop

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomContainer.Glyph
Summary
  Specifies an image to display on the control.
Description
  Use Glyph to specify an image to display on the control. When Glyph contains an image, the Caption
  is adjusted so it appears to the right of the image.
See Also
  TJvXPCustomContainer.GlyphLayout

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomContainer.GlyphLayout
Summary
  Specifies how the Glyph is aligned in the control.
Description
  Set GlyphLayout to specify how the image in Glyph is aligned within the control.
See Also
  TJvXPCustomContainer.Glyph

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomContainer.Layout
Summary
  Specifies the vertical placement of the text within the control.
Description
  Set Layout to specify how the text of the control is placed within the ClientRect of the control.
  Layout is the vertical analog to the Alignment property.
See Also
  Caption

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomContainer.OnEnabledChanged
Summary
  Occurs when the Enabled state changes.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnEnabledChanged to take specific action when the control's Enabled state
  has changed.
See Also
  Enabled

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomContainer.OnPaint
Summary
  Occurs when the control needs to be painted.
Description
  Use OnPaint to perform special processing when the control is redrawn. Any special painting on the
  control should be done in this event. OnPaint occurs after the borders are drawn but before the
  image and text of the control.
Parameters
  Sender  - The control that triggered the event.
  Rect    - The area to draw in.
  ACanvas - The canvas to draw on.
  AFont   - The font to use for text drawing. You can change the properties of AFont to change the
         way the default text is drawn.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomContainer.ShowBoundLines
Summary
  Specifies whether borders are shown or not.
Description
  Use ShowBoundLines to specify whether borders are shown or not.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomContainer.ShowCaption
Summary
  Specifies whether the control's caption is drawn at run-time.
Description
  Use ShowCaption to specify whether the control's caption is drawn at run-time.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomContainer.Spacing
Summary
  Determines where the image and text appear on the control.
Description
  Use Spacing to specify where the image and text appear on the control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomContainer.WordWrap
Summary
  Determines whether the control inserts soft carriage returns so text wraps at the right margin.
Description
  Use WordWrap to specify how the text is drawn when it doesn't fit inside the control. If WordWrap
  is true, the text will be wrapped to as many lines as needed to fit the text inside the control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPEnabledMode
<TITLE TJvXPEnabledMode type>
Summary
  Specifies how changes to the Enabled property propagates to child controls.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPEnabledMode.emAffectChilds
Changing Enabled also changes Enabled of all child controls.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPEnabledMode.emNormal
Changing Enabled does not affect child controls.

